<topic id='business_definition_emergency_care_initial_assessment_time.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Emergency Care Initial Assessment Time - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_emergency_care_initial_assessment_time">Emergency Care Initial Assessment Time</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity_date_time">ACTIVITY DATE TIME</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_emergency_care_initial_assessment_time">Emergency Care Initial Assessment Time</xref>
 is the time that the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is first assessed in the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_emergency_care_department">Emergency Care Department</xref>.        </p>
    <p>An initial assessment would include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <div>
          <p>
the taking of a brief 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 medical history                    </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div>
          <p>pain assessment</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div>
          <p>early warning scores (including vital signs).</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
The assessment should be conducted by a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>
 who has received appropriate training.        </p>
    <p>
Note that for piloting purposes only, an 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_emergency_care_initial_assessment_time">Emergency Care Initial Assessment Time</xref>
 may also be the Ambulatory Emergency Care Initial Assessment Time.        </p>
  </div>
</body>
